It all indicates, space was being used as a quarantine place for coronavirus.
In total, since the outbreak began, until midnight on Friday (16h00 hours on Wednesday, in Lisbon), 80,651 cases were confirmed in mainland China. Of these, 22,177 remain infected, of which 5,489 are in serious condition. This shows that more than half of the infected responded positively to treatment and received high. The Chinese authorities even said that 55,4404 were cured so far.
The outbreak of Covid-19, detected in December, China, and that can cause respiratory infections such as pneumonia, caused more than 3,600 dead and infected more than 100,000 people in 92 countries and territories.
In Portugal, the General Directorate of Health (DGS) confirmed 13 cases of infection so far, but RTP guarantees that there are two more cases at the São João Hospital in Porto.
The World Health Organization (WHO) declared the outbreak of Covid-19 as an international public health emergency and increased the risk to "very high."
